Nordic Sugar A/S, a Danish unit of
 Germany â€™s Nordzucker AG, said Thomas B. Olsen is resigning as
managing director.  Olsen will leave March 15, the Copenhagen-based company
said today in a statement on its  website . He joined Nordic Sugar
in 1988, it showed. Mats Liljestam, chief marketing officer at
Nordzucker, has been named to replace Olsen for now.  Dorthe Lindgreen, a communications manager at the Danish
company, confirmed the statement by phone today. Nordic Sugar
has factories in Denmark, Sweden, Finland and  Lithuania .  To contact the reporter on this story:
